    <item>
      <title>Nichiren Buddhism and Vegetarianism</title>
      <link>https://lotusbuddhism.info/faq/buddhism-vegetarianism/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://lotusbuddhism.info/faq/buddhism-vegetarianism/</guid>
      <description>Traditional views in various societies tend to merge the image of “Buddhist” as being “Vegetarian”. Where did this idea come from?
Tracing back the history of Buddhism, we find that the Brahmin, or “the seekers of the truth” in ancient India - where Shakyamuni Buddha lived – were all devoted individuals who chose to dwell in forests and retreats, spending their time in deep meditation and in teachings of their disciples.</description>
